KwaZulu-Natal is trying to revive its tourism sector. But the question is, will travellers visit following big disasters such as the recent floods and July unrest. A winter campaign is hoping to attract visitors and get KZN back on the list of top domestic travel destinations. The government says rebuilding is well underway but how long will this take? eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli has this story. DURBAN - KwaZulu Natal is trying to revive its tourism sector. But the question is: Will travellers visit following big disasters such as the recent floods and July unrest? WATCH: Tourism in SA | Plan to assist affected businesses A winter campaign is hoping to attract visitors and get KwaZulu-Natal back on the list of top domestic travel destinations. The July season is expected to be a big month for tourism in the province, with over 6,000 international travellers expected. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.